# Project CLAUDE.md

## SkillLord Configuration

This project uses SkillLord with the **full** profile for a Next.js + API fullstack application.

## Active Skills

### Tier 1 — Core (always loaded)
- debugging, code-review, tdd-workflow, testing
- frontend-development, web-frameworks, react-best-practices, ui-styling
- backend-development, api-design, databases
- devops, security-review, sequential-thinking, research

### Tier 2 — On-Demand
- frontend-patterns, backend-patterns, coding-standards
- e2e-testing, deployment-patterns, docker-patterns
- postgres-patterns, database-migrations
- better-auth, payment-integration
- mcp-management, claude-code, planning
- verification-loop, strategic-compact

### Tier 3 — Specialty (as needed)
- vercel-deploy, agentic-engineering

## Workflows
- Follow TDD approach: write tests first, then implement
- Run `/audit` before every PR
- Use `/route` when unsure which skill applies
- Run `/verify` before merging to main
- Use `/cook` for end-to-end feature implementation

## Commands
- `/plan` → Plan features and architecture
- `/code` → Start coding an existing plan
- `/test` → Run tests and analyze coverage
- `/fix` → Fix issues (variants: fix:fast, fix:hard, fix:ci, fix:test, fix:types, fix:ui, fix:logs)
- `/tdd` → Test-driven development workflow
- `/cook` → Implement features end-to-end
- `/debug` → Deep issue analysis
- `/review` → Code review with security focus
- `/audit` → Run quality checks
- `/e2e` → Generate and run Playwright E2E tests
- `/scout` → Search and explore codebase
- `/bootstrap` → Initialize new project structure
- `/brainstorm` → Explore solution approaches
- `/build-fix` → Fix build and type errors
- `/evolve` → Iterative feature development
- `/route` → Get skill recommendations

## Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router, RSC)
- TypeScript 5.x
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- PostgreSQL + Prisma ORM
- Better Auth for authentication
- Playwright for E2E testing
- Vercel for deployment
- Turborepo for monorepo management
